A 30-year-old construction worker was struck down by a light delivery vehicle, crushing her between concrete blocks, on Monday. Netcare 911 said they responded to the incident on the N3, Ashburton, on Monday afternoon. According to a statement by Netcare 911 spokesperson Shawn Herbst, the woman sustained critical injuries. "The patient was treated on scene by an emergency care practitioner. Due to the nature of the woman's injuries, a Netcare 911 helicopter was dispatched to airlift the patient to a specialised facility,‚Äù said Herbst.